uml_parser.collectors

Class ModelCollector

  • java.lang.Object
    • bnf_parser.collectors.Collector
      • uml_parser.collectors.ModelCollector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Model

    public class ModelCollector
extends Collector
implements Model
    This class collects a mix of ClassContentCollector, AssociationCollector, GeneralizationCollector and AggregationCollector declarations and use them to represent a UML schema.
    Author:
    Hubert Lemelin

      • addChild

        public void addChild(Collector collector,
                     int index)
        Expects one StringCollector containing the identifier (name) of the model and any of ClassContentCollector, AssociationCollector, GeneralizationCollector and AggregationCollector.
        Specified by:
        addChild in class Collector
        Parameters:
        collector - The collector returned by the parser. It might be null.
        index - A custom index defined when creating the current rule to identify more easily a collector, which is particularly useful when many Collector instances are used, and even more useful when some instances are allowed to be missing (minOccurences = 0).
        See Also:
        Collector.addChild(Collector, int)
